<br>
It boils down to a couple things - whether things are fair, and the only way for a person to express strong disapproval is to vote with their feet.<br>
<br>
The normal ethic is:<br>
<br>
- don't care too much about loot, in that &quot;I'm only going because I want some item&quot;.<br>
<br>
- if you *do* have loot issues, ask in advance. For example, the following wouldn't be too bad (if true):<br>
/tell raidleader I'm choosing between going on the raid and something fun in RL. To be honest I'm sick of that place and the main reason I'd go is to try for the item, if you need the help. Do you need the help, and what would your loot rules be? I understand if you don't want someone there who is there for the item!<br>
<br>
